Let's fix the errors in your program step by step:

## 1. Typo in `document.getAnimations`
You wrote:
```js
let n3 = document.getAnimations("t3").value;
```
It should be:
```js
let n3 = document.getElementById("t3").value;
```

## 2. Variable Names Mismatch
You have variables `n1`, `n2`, `n3`, but in the output you're using `num1`, `num2`, `num3`, which are undefined.

Fix: Change all `num1`, `num2`, `num3` to `n1`, `n2`, `n3`.

## 3. Numeric Comparison Issue
The values from input fields are **strings**, so comparing them (`'11' > '2'` is `false` in JS).  
Fix: Use `Number()` or `parseFloat()` to convert the inputs to numbers.

## 4. Little Formatting
Add a space at the end of "The largest is".

---

## **CORRECTED CODE**
```html
<p>Write a program to find the largest number among 3 numbers.</p>
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter 1st number" id="t1">
<br>
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter 2nd number" id="t2">
<br>
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter 3rd number" id="t3">
<button onclick="check()">Check</button>
<h3 id="ans">The largest number is</h3>
<script>
    function check() {
        let n1 = Number(document.getElementById("t1").value);
        let n2 = Number(document.getElementById("t2").value);
        let n3 = Number(document.getElementById("t3").value);

        let largest;
        if (n1 > n2 && n1 > n3) {
            largest = n1;
        } else if (n2 > n3) {
            largest = n2;
        } else {
            largest = n3;
        }
        document.getElementById("ans").innerHTML = "The largest is " + largest;
    }
</script>
```

