Write a js code block to build a pyramid in minecraft using sandstone, the pyramid should be large and centered just like a real pyramid.

answer:
Absolutely! Below is a JavaScript code block (for a Minecraft bot like [mineflayer](https://github.com/PrismarineJS/mineflayer)), that will build a large, properly centered pyramid with even layers, using **sandstone**.

This code assumes:

- You have access to `world.getPosition(bot)` to get the starting position.
- Your `skills.placeBlock(bot, block, x, y, z)` places a block at that location.
- The code runs inside an `async` function.

---

```js
const position = world.getPosition(bot);
const centerX = Math.floor(position.x);
const baseY = Math.floor(position.y);
const centerZ = Math.floor(position.z);

const size = 15; // Length of one pyramid side (must be odd for perfect centering)
const height = Math.ceil(size / 2); // Height of pyramid

for (let layer = 0; layer < height; layer++) {
    const layerY = baseY + layer;
    const layerHalf = Math.floor(size / 2) - layer;
    const minX = centerX - layerHalf;
    const maxX = centerX + layerHalf;
    const minZ = centerZ - layerHalf;
    const maxZ = centerZ + layerHalf;

    for (let x = minX; x <= maxX; x++) {
        for (let z = minZ; z <= maxZ; z++) {
            // Only build the perimeter for hollow pyramid (optional)
            if (
                x === minX ||
                x === maxX ||
                z === minZ ||
                z === maxZ
            ) {
                await skills.placeBlock(bot, 'sandstone', x, layerY, z);
            }
            // If you want a solid pyramid instead, comment out the above if block and uncomment the line below
            // await skills.placeBlock(bot, 'sandstone', x, layerY, z);
        }
    }
}
```

**Tips:**
- Adjust `size` for a bigger or smaller base (must be odd for perfect centering).
- For a **solid** pyramid (not hollow), place `await skills.placeBlock(...)` for every x/z, not just the perimeter.

