answer:
Absolutely! Here’s an end-to-end guide for a “modern” NixOS setup with the technologies you requested:

---

## 0. **Assumptions**

- You just finished installing NixOS, and can log in as your regular user (let’s say: `youruser`)
- You have root permissions on this machine, and want to use the latest **stable** channel (let’s say 24.05)
- You want a modern desktop with GNOME/Wayland, Neovim, VSCode, Zed, Brave, Bitwarden, Home Manager, and 10+ standard CLI tools

---

## 1. **Bootstrap Flakes Support & Enable Experimental Features**

Nix Flakes are **experimental**, so you’ll want to enable them for both root and your user:

Edit `/etc/nix/nix.conf` and add:

```conf
experimental-features = nix-command flakes
```

*(If the file doesn’t exist, create it.)*

---

## 2. **Install Nix Flakes Support for Your User**

Make sure you can use `nix` CLI as *your user*, not just root. NixOS comes with it by default, but if you ever see a warning, you may want to relog or run:

```sh
sudo nixos-rebuild switch
```

---

## 3. **Initialize a Flake-based Configuration**

Let’s make a new config repository in your home:

```sh
cd ~
git init nixos-config
cd nixos-config
```

#### Scaffold a basic flake:

```sh
nix flake init -t github:nix-community/nix-flake-templates#simple
```

But better yet, since we want both **system** and **home** management, delete the default `flake.nix` and create your own structure:

### Structure:

```
nixos-config/
├── flake.nix
├── flake.lock
├── system/
│   └── configuration.nix
└── home/
    └── home.nix
```

---

## 4. **Write Your Flake Configuration**

Here’s a full `flake.nix` suitable for your specified stack. It declares both a NixOS system and a Home Manager setup.

### `flake.nix`:

```nix
{
  description = "My flake-powered NixOS and Home Manager configuration";

  inputs = {
    nixpkgs.url = "github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixos-24.05";
    home-manager = {
      url = "github:nix-community/home-manager/release-24.05";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
  };

  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, home-manager }:
    let
      system = "x86_64-linux";
      username = "youruser";  # <=== change to your user!
      hostname = "nixos";     # <=== change as desired!
    in
    {
      nixosConfigurations.${hostname} = nixpkgs.lib.nixosSystem {
        inherit system;
        specialArgs = {
          inherit hostname username;
        };
        modules = [
          ./system/configuration.nix
          home-manager.nixosModules.home-manager
          {
            home-manager.useGlobalPkgs = true;
            home-manager.useUserPackages = true;
            home-manager.users.${username} = import ./home/home.nix;
          }
        ];
      };
    };
}
```

---

### `system/configuration.nix` (NixOS config)

```nix
{ config, pkgs, hostname, username, ... }:

{
  networking.hostName = hostname;
  time.timeZone = "Europe/Berlin"; # <-- adjust to your timezone!
  i18n.defaultLocale = "en_US.UTF-8";

  services.xserver = {
    enable = true;
    displayManager.gdm.enable = true;
    desktopManager.gnome.enable = true;
    # auto enable wayland with GDM for GNOME
    displayManager.gdm.wayland = true;
  };

  environment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [
    git
    wget
    curl
    htop
    unzip
    zip
    tree
    ripgrep
    fd
    jq
    gnupg
    psmisc
  ];

  users.users.${username} = {
    isNormalUser = true;
    extraGroups = [ "wheel" "audio" "video" "networkmanager" ]; # wheel=sudo
    shell = pkgs.zsh;
  };

  programs.zsh.enable = true;
  services.openssh.enable = true;

  # Networking
  networking.networkmanager.enable = true;

  # Sound
  sound.enable = true;
  hardware.pulseaudio.enable = false;
  services.pipewire = {
    enable = true;
    audio.enable = true;
    pulse.enable = true;
    wireplumber.enable = true;
  };

  # Allow unfree packages
  nixpkgs.config.allowUnfree = true;

  # Enable Flakes systemwide
  nix.extraOptions = ''
    experimental-features = nix-command flakes
  '';

  # Nice fonts
  fonts.fonts = with pkgs; [
    noto-fonts
    noto-fonts-cjk
    noto-fonts-emoji
    (nerdfonts.override { fonts = [ "JetBrainsMono" ]; })
  ];

  # Gnome tweaks
  environment.gnome.excludePackages = (with pkgs; [
    gnome-photos
    gnome-maps
    gnome-music
    gnome-weather
    gnome-calendar
    gnome-contacts
    gnome-todo
    gnome-characters
    gnome-clocks
    gnome-logs
    gnome-tour
  ]);
}
```

---

### `home/home.nix` (Home Manager config)

```nix
{ config, pkgs, ... }:

{
  home.username = "youruser";  # <--- update!
  home.homeDirectory = "/home/youruser"; # <--- update!
  programs.home-manager.enable = true;

  # Shell config
  programs.zsh = {
    enable = true;
    autosuggestion.enable = true;
    syntaxHighlighting.enable = true;
    oh-my-zsh = {
      enable = true;
      plugins = [ "git" "vi-mode" ];
      theme = "agnoster";
    };
  };

  # Neovim
  programs.neovim = {
    enable = true;
    viAlias = true;
    vimAlias = true;
  };

  # Graphical apps
  home.packages = with pkgs; [
    zed-editor
    vscode
    brave
    bitwarden
  ];

  # Home-manager managed git config
  programs.git = {
    enable = true;
    userName = "Your Name";
    userEmail = "your@email.com";
  };

  # Other user CLI stuff (complementary)
  home.sessionVariables = {
    EDITOR = "nvim";
    BROWSER = "brave";
  };
}
```

---

## 5. **Apply Your Flake!**

Now, from the root of your `nixos-config` directory, do:

```sh
sudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake .#<hostname>
```
replace `<hostname>` with the one in your flake (e.g., `nixos`).

*If prompted, allow root to access your repo, or run as root.*

---

## 6. **What You Get**

- **NixOS** using a modern *flake* setup.
- **GNOME 46** running with **Wayland** (by default with GDM)
- **Zsh** as your shell (with oh-my-zsh plugins and themes)
- **Neovim, VS Code, Zed Editor, Brave browser, Bitwarden** installed user-scoped via Home Manager.
- **Standard CLI tools** (curl, fd, ripgrep, jq, zip, unzip, jq, gnupg, tree, htop, psmisc)
- **pipewire** for modern audio stack
- **Tidied Gnome** (no bloatware)
- **Fonts**: JetBrainsMono NerdFont for coding
- Easily reproducible, upgradable configuration

---

## 7. **Future Changes**

To change packages/env, just edit the relevant files and rerun:

```sh
sudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake .#<hostname>
```

You can also build a new system generation before switching:

```sh
sudo nixos-rebuild build --flake .#<hostname>
sudo ./result/bin/switch-to-configuration switch
```

---

## 8. **Why flake + Home Manager?**

- **Flakes**: lock all versions and channels, ensure reproducibility
- **Home Manager**: separates user-level (dotfiles, apps, etc) from system-level (services, kernel, drivers, etc)
- Easily put this repo in Git! (Highly recommended.)

---

## 9. **References**

- [NixOS Flakes](https://nixos.org/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-flake.html)
- [Home Manager](https://nix-community.github.io/home-manager/)
- [NixOS Modules](https://search.nixos.org/options)

---

**If you need to add or remove more apps, just edit `home.nix`!**

You now have a future-proof, flake-based, Home Manager-driven NixOS desktop!

